3
00:00:17,950 --> 00:00:21,800
Do we know something about how much scores vary around that mean?

4
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:26,560
To find this out, we have to give the test to a large number of people.

5
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:30,320
Look at their scores on the test and work out what their average score is, and how much

6
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:33,080
variation there is around that average.

7
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:37,770
In doing this, it&#39;s important to keep in mind what those people are like.

8
00:00:37,770 --> 00:00:42,010
For example, if I&#39;m interested in developing an intelligence test for university students,

9
00:00:42,010 --> 00:00:46,650
I would standardise the test on a large sample of university students.

10
00:00:46,650 --> 00:00:51,060
If I wanted to develop a test for university students, imagine that instead of standardising

